      "content": "Ah, you're right! I apologize for the distraction. Let's get straight to the math without the goblin nonsense.\n\nHere is the formula for **Straight-Line Depreciation**:\n\n$$ \\text{Annual Depreciation Expense} = \\frac{\\text{Cost of Asset} - \\text{Salvage Value}}{\\text{Useful Life}} $$\n\n**Example Calculation:**\n*   **Cost:** $50,000\n*   **Salvage Value:** $5,000\n*   **Useful Life:** 5 years\n\n$$ \\text{Depreciation} = \\frac{50,000 - 5,000}{5} = \\frac{45,000}{5} = 9,000 $$\n\n**Answer:** $9,000 per year.\n\nI hope that clears things up for your notes!",
